				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204686" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1557624935 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 May 2019 01:35</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4245914">
									

<p>My stance on the 'established' esoteric classes and 'expanded' is decidedly negative. In universe, they make no sense because their nicheness is the exact opposite of what the object class is supposed to achieve &#8212; a standardized at-a-glance assessment of the difficulty of containing an object. Out of universe, they're pointless gimmicks used to class an object that inevitably fits perfectly well within the existing Safe-Euclid-Keter-Thaumiel-Explained-Neutralized framework.</p>

							</div>

								
