			<div class="content" id="post-content-4246613">
									

<p>The Established table was created to help authors trying to find an esoteric class that might apply to their SCP. It is unlikely any new article will fit the definitions of Yesod and Netzach, and <tt>UNDEFINED</tt> is more the result of the anti-memetic qualities of the SCP it appears in. However, an author could write an SCP that is a direct threat to the O5s, broken into pieces, used to create SCPs, pending classification, debated, and containing no object class.</p>
<p>This list is definitely for anything placed in the object class line. Would you support a separate table for non-object classes caused by memes/infohazards? I'm not willing to separate Archon and Pending, though. While Pending isn't a true object class in-universe, it's what appears in the articles and it isn't the result of any anomalous manipulation.</p>

